ix.util.context
Class ContextMultiHashMap

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      java.util.HashMap
          ix.util.MultiHashMap
              ix.util.context.ContextMultiHashMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
ContextMultiMap, MultiMap, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map
public class ContextMultiHashMap
extends MultiHashMap
implements ContextMultiMap

Maps a key to a context-dependent list. Note that the mapping is not itself context-dependent -- a given key maps to the same list regardless of context -- but what the list contains is context-dependent.

See Also:
LLQueue, Serialized Form
